/* /find-an-accountant/washington/ — t-state-pillar PILLAR. Washington is a CORE state built to the 6-essentials depth
 * (pillar + quickbooks-accountant + small-business-accountant + quickbooks-cleanup + quickbooks-setup +
 * bookkeeping-services); every absent service/industry ROUTES TO GLOBAL. WA is an areaServed-ONLY state: TechBrot serves
 * Washington remotely, so this pillar carries NO street address, NO PostalAddress, NO geo, NO LocalBusiness node, and NO
 * hasMap (all states are areaServed-only (no street address)). Service + areaServed (State of Washington + named metros) only; provider =
 * #organization. Mirrors the PA/NJ/MD/VA/OH/MI/GA/NC/AZ/TN core-state exemplars: OMITS `ecosystem`; `industries` cards ->
 * GLOBAL /accounting/industries/*; 5 SERVICE cards = the WA children; `cities` name+county with NO href; pricing rows ->
 * 5 children + global. Washington STARTS Wave D (Seattle tech / Boeing aerospace / Amazon e-commerce economy).
 *
 * WASHINGTON FACTS (verified 2026-06-26 against the WA Dept of Revenue, ESD/Paid Leave, WA Cares — see _build/strategy/WA-FACTS.md):
 *  · NO individual AND no corporate income tax — the headline draw. So there is NO state income-tax withholding on payroll.
 *    But "no income tax" is not "low tax" — the state raises revenue through the B&O tax, a high combined sales/use tax,
 *    and (since 2022) a capital-gains tax.
 *  · Business & Occupation (B&O) tax — the WA-distinct hook and the REAL business tax: a GROSS-RECEIPTS tax by
 *    classification (50+) with NO deduction for labor, materials, rent, or any cost of doing business — so even a
 *    break-even business owes it. Retailing 0.471%, Wholesaling 0.484%, Manufacturing 0.484%; Service & Other Activities
 *    TIERED (eff Oct 1, 2025): 1.5% under $1M prior-year taxable income, 1.75% $1M to under $5M, and a higher top tier at
 *    $5M+ (kept qualitative). Plus CITY B&O: many cities (Seattle, Tacoma, Bellevue, Everett) levy their own local B&O,
 *    administered by the city (not DOR) — kept qualitative.
 *  · High combined sales/use tax — among the highest in the US: 6.5% STATE rate plus local, so combined commonly lands
 *    ~8.5–10.5% by location; destination-based. Use tax mirrors it on untaxed purchases (notably near the Oregon border,
 *    since Oregon has no sales tax).
 *  · Capital-gains tax — the 2022 catch on a "no-income-tax" state: a 7% tax on long-term capital gains above a standard
 *    deduction ($278,000 for 2025), plus an additional 2.9% on the excess over $1M. Real estate, retirement-account
 *    assets, and assets used in a trade or business are exempt. It is an INDIVIDUAL excise tax on owners — advisory and
 *    coordination only; TechBrot does not file it.
 *  · WA payroll premiums (no income-tax withholding, but two premiums): PFML — 2026 premium 1.13% of wages, split
 *    employer 28.57% / employee 71.43%; employers with fewer than 50 employees are not required to pay the employer share.
 *    WA Cares — 0.58% of gross wages, paid entirely by the employee (0.58% for 2025 and 2026).
 *  · Geography — 39 counties; the economy is Puget-Sound-centric (King, Pierce, Snohomish), with Spokane and the
 *    Yakima/Tri-Cities belt anchoring Eastern Washington. Metros: Seattle (King; cloud, tech, maritime, HQs), Spokane
 *    (Spokane; Eastern-WA hub), Tacoma (Pierce; port, logistics, manufacturing), Vancouver (Clark; across the Columbia
 *    from Portland, Oregon — the no-sales-tax-border nuance), Bellevue (King; tech), Everett (Snohomish; Boeing
 *    aerospace), Kent (King; warehousing/distribution), Olympia (Thurston; state capital), Bellingham (Whatcom; named in
 *    prose only).
 *
 * HONESTY: TechBrot is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor + bookkeeping firm, NOT affiliated with Intuit. It
 * does NOT file WA or federal returns, the B&O / Combined Excise Tax Return, the sales-tax return, the capital-gains tax,
 * or the city B&O return as agent; it keeps the books and coordinates with the client's CPA/EA and the Washington Dept of
 * Revenue. Reviews are ONLY the 2 real Clutch reviews (Heidi Schubert, Barbara Best) — no invented reviewers, no
 * AggregateRating. Outcomes/scenarios are explicitly representative composites — never real-client claims. No
 * founder/personal name in visible content; David Westgate appears only as the named lead ProAdvisor/operator. The no
 * income tax (and no state withholding), the B&O rates (retailing 0.471%, wholesaling/manufacturing 0.484%, service
 * tiered 1.5%/1.75%/top), the 6.5% state sales tax, the 7% capital-gains tax (+2.9% over $1M, $278k 2025 deduction), the
 * PFML 1.13% (2026), and the WA Cares 0.58% are VERIFIED and stated; specific combined local sales-tax rates, city B&O
 * rates, and the exact service-B&O top tier are framed qualitatively. */
function stripTags(html){return html.replace(/<[^>]+>/g,"").replace(/&rsquo;/g,"’").replace(/&lsquo;/g,"‘").replace(/&ldquo;/g,"“").replace(/&rdquo;/g,"”").replace(/&mdash;/g,"—").replace(/&ndash;/g,"–").replace(/&rarr;/g,"→").replace(/&amp;/g,"&").replace(/&nbsp;/g," ").replace(/&middot;/g,"·").replace(/&times;/g,"×").replace(/\s+/g," ").trim();}

